@database Etch-a-Sketch
@remark $VER: Etch-a-Sketch AmigaGuide® doc file v1.0

@node main "Etch-a-Sketch"
Etch-a-Sketch is a small program for simulating the well-known drawing toy,
"Etch-a-Sketch". It is intended solely for entertainment purposes. It was
written by me, JIPsoft (Joona I Palaste) in April 1998 with DICE C and
GadToolsBox.

Further info:
    - @{"Installation" link "install"}
    - @{"Usage       " link "use"}
    - @{"Requirements" link "require"}
    - @{"Author      " link "author"}
    - @{"Copyrights  " link "copyrights"}
    - @{"History     " link "history"}
@endnode

@node install "Installation"
Installation is simple: copy the files to wherever you want to. The program file
"Etch-a-Sketch.exe" is the only file you need to run the program.
@endnode

@node use "Usage"
To start the program, either double-click on the icon or type the program name
from AmigaDOS. A window will then open, with the drawing area and controls.
Dragging the sliders draws on the drawing area. You can select a new colour from
the palette below the drawing area. (The palette automatically adapts to the
screen depth when started.) To exit the program, click on the close window
gadget.
@endnode

@node require "Requirements"
Etch-a-Sketch requires:
    - An Amiga® computer.
    - Workbench 3.0 or above (could also work with 2.0, but not tested yet).
    - The libraries dos.library, intuition.library, graphics.library and
      gadtools.library (should be included in any Workbench 3.x).
    - Electricity.
@endnode

